			<VARNAME>SECTACCE</VARNAME>
			<SENTIMENT>Negative</SENTIMENT>
			<VALUE>This was supposed to be an in-person visit. I was called the afternoon before my appointment to change it to telecare. I don't mind doing telecare appointments, but it's become common for me to get a last minute appointment change for all Keck USC appointments and I've had experiences where if I'm unable to answer the call I'm randomly assigned a new appointment date/time. At that point it's incredibly difficult to reach someone again to reschedule, because I have to drive over an hour and make work arrangements for all appointments. It's also resulted in delays of care. It's to the point that I'm seriously considering switching to Scripps in San Diego for my care.</VALUE>
		</RESPONSE>
		<RESPONSE>
			<VARNAME>SECTCARE</VARNAME>
			<SENTIMENT>Mixed</SENTIMENT>
			<VALUE>Dr. Han is great about providing easily understandable explanations, but she starts with explanations before asking questions. This results in extended discussion time with her explaining things the patient already knows. There is also a lack of communication between providers  in different departments at Keck USC. I expect this when providers are in different health systems, but not when I'm told I'm going to a center for excellence for my specific condition and I was referred to Dr. Han for a related condition.</VALUE>
		</RESPONSE>
		<RESPONSE>
			<VARNAME>SECTOVER</VARNAME>
			<SENTIMENT>Mixed</SENTIMENT>
			<VALUE>It works and I'm glad it exists. The technology still needs improvement.</VALUE>
		</RESPONSE>
		<RESPONSE>
			<VARNAME>SECTTELE</VARNAME>
			<SENTIMENT>Negative</SENTIMENT>
			<VALUE>I wish there was a way to turn off video while waiting for the provider. I had a 20 minute wait and the entire time the video was live. I also was unable to use any other windows on my device while waiting because it would automatically disconnect the call.</VALUE>
		</RESPONSE>
